  checkpoint {
    user_intent: "Phase 1: Landing Page Development\n\nThe user\'s main goal is to develop the landing page for a media tracking application. This involves setting up the project structure, defining the application\'s core types, creating a backend server for data persistence, and implementing the UI for the landing page, including a hero section and recent activity display. The user also aims to establish navigation and a basic layout for the application."
    intent_only: true
    included_step_index_end: 14
    conversation_log_uris: "file:///.gemini/antigravity/brain/c67eefdb-000d-4f73-b7f5-46dfe25e08dd/.system_generated/logs/overview.txt"
    user_requests: "Here is the full initial file tree for the application:\n/.env.example\n/.gitignore\n/index.html\n/metadata.json\n/package.json\n/src/App.tsx\n/src/index.css\n/src/main.tsx\n/tsconfig.json\n/vite.config.ts\n\nThe following dependencies are installed:\n@google/genai: ^1.29.0\n@tailwindcss/vite: ^4.1.14\n@vitejs/plugin-react: ^5.0.4\nbetter-sqlite3: ^12.4.1\ndotenv: ^17.2.3\nexpress: ^4.21.2\nlucide-react: ^0.546.0\nmotion: ^12.23.24\nreact: ^19.0.0\nreact-dom: ^19.0.0\nvite: ^6.2.0\n\nThe following devDependencies are installed:\n@types/express: ^4.17.21\n@types/node: ^22.14.0\nautoprefixer: ^10.4.21\ntailwindcss: ^4.1.14\ntsx: ^4.21.0\ntypescript: ~5.8.2\nvite: ^6.2.0\n\nKey file contents:\n\n--- /.env.example ---\n```\n# GEMINI_API_KEY: Required for Gemini AI API calls.\n# AI Studio automatically injects this at runtime from user secrets.\n# Users configure this via the Secrets panel in the AI Studio UI.\nGEMINI_API_KEY=\"MY_GEMINI_API_KEY\"\n\n# APP_URL: The URL where this applet is hosted.\n# AI Studio automatically injects this at runtime with the Cloud Run service URL.\n# Used for self-referential links, OAuth callbacks, and API endpoints.\nAPP_URL=\"MY_APP_URL\"\n\n```\n\n--- /index.html ---\n```html\n<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n    <title>My Google AI Studio App</title>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <div id=\"root\"></div>\n    <script type=\"module\" src=\"/src/main.tsx\"></script>\n  </body>\n</html>\n\n\n```\n\n--- /metadata.json ---\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"\",\n  \"description\": \"\",\n  \"requestFramePermissions\": []\n}\n\n```\n\n--- /src/App.tsx ---\n```typescript\n/**\n * @license\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0\n */\n\nexport default function App() {\n  return <div></div>;\n}\n\n```\n\n--- /src/index.css ---\n```css\n@import \"tailwindcss\";\n\n```\n\n--- /src/main.tsx ---\n```typescript\nimport {StrictMode} from \'react\';\nimport {createRoot} from \'react-dom/client\';\nimport App from \'./App.tsx\';\nimport \'./index.css\';\n\ncreateRoot(document.getElementById(\'root\')!).render(\n  <StrictMode>\n    <App />\n  </StrictMode>,\n);\n\n```\n\n--- /tsconfig.json ---\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"experimentalDecorators\": true,\n    \"useDefineForClassFields\": false,\n    \"module\": \"ESNext\",\n    \"lib\": [\n      \"ES2022\",\n      \"DOM\",\n      \"DOM.Iterable\"\n    ],\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"bundler\",\n    \"isolatedModules\": true,\n    \"moduleDetection\": \"force\",\n    \"allowJs\": true,\n    \"jsx\": \"react-jsx\",\n    \"paths\": {\n      \"@/*\": [\n        \"./*\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"allowImportingTsExtensions\": true,\n    \"noEmit\": true\n  }\n}\n\n```\n\n--- /vite.config.ts ---\n```typescript\nimport tailwindcss from \'@tailwindcss/vite\';\nimport react from \'@vitejs/plugin-react\';\nimport path from \'path\';\nimport {defineConfig, loadEnv} from \'vite\';\n\nexport default defineConfig(({mode}) => {\n  const env = loadEnv(mode, \'.\', \'\');\n  return {\n    plugins: [react(), tailwindcss()],\n    define: {\n      \'process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY\': JSON.stringify(env.GEMINI_API_KEY),\n    },\n    resolve: {\n      alias: {\n        \'@\': path.resolve(__dirname, \'.\'),\n      },\n    },\n    server: {\n      // HMR is disabled in AI Studio via DISABLE_HMR env var.\n      // Do not modify\303\242\302\200\302\224file watching is disabled to prevent flickering during agent edits.\n      hmr: process.env.DISABLE_HMR !== \'true\',\n    },\n  };\n});\n\n```"
    user_requests: "Act as a Senior Full-Stack Software Engineer and UI/UX Designer. Your goal is to guide me through the development of a comprehensive \"Media Tracker\" web application designed to catalog movies, series, documentaries, books, and console games.\n\nWe will follow a structured, iterative development process. You are to lead the architecture and provide code snippets, structure, and design recommendations for each phase.\n\nProject Phases:\n\nPhase 1: Landing Page Architecture: Design an engaging, clean, and modern landing page. Define the layout, navigation, and overall user experience.\n\nPhase 2: Dynamic Input System: Develop a robust, intuitive input interface allowing for quick entry of new media items, including fields for media type, title, status (planned, watching, completed), and personal rating.\n\nPhase 3: Archive & Analytics Dashboard: Create an archive view that aggregates consumption data, enabling users to visualize their history filtered by month and media category.\n\nYour Instructions for each step:\n\nProvide clean, modular, and well-commented code (HTML/CSS/JS or the framework of your choice).\n\nExplain the technical rationale behind your design decisions.\n\nSuggest best practices for data management and persistence.\n\nEnsure the design is responsive and user-friendly.\n\nDevelopment Constraints:\n\nPrioritize a minimalist, clean aesthetic.\n\nFocus on logical data structure to allow for seamless sorting and filtering across all media categories.\n\nMaintain a professional and helpful tone.\n\nWe will begin with Phase 1. Please propose a layout strategy for the landing page, including key UI elements that define the app\'s purpose, and provide the initial code structure."
    user_requests: "Act as a Senior Full-Stack Software Engineer and UI/UX Designer. Your goal is to guide me through the development of a comprehensive \"Media Tracker\" web application designed to catalog movies, series, documentaries, books, and console games.\n\nWe will follow a structured, iterative development process. You are to lead the architecture and provide code snippets, structure, and design recommendations for each phase.\n\nProject Phases:\n\nPhase 1: Landing Page Architecture: Design an engaging, clean, and modern landing page. Define the layout, navigation, and overall user experience.\n\nPhase 2: Dynamic Input System: Develop a robust, intuitive input interface allowing for quick entry of new media items, including fields for media type, title, status (planned, watching, completed), and personal rating.\n\nPhase 3: Archive & Analytics Dashboard: Create an archive view that aggregates consumption data, enabling users to visualize their history filtered by month and media category.\n\nYour Instructions for each step:\n\nProvide clean, modular, and well-commented code (HTML/CSS/JS or the framework of your choice).\n\nExplain the technical rationale behind your design decisions.\n\nSuggest best practices for data management and persistence.\n\nEnsure the design is responsive and user-friendly.\n\nDevelopment Constraints:\n\nPrioritize a minimalist, clean aesthetic.\n\nFocus on logical data structure to allow for seamless sorting and filtering across all media categories.\n\nMaintain a professional and helpful tone.\n\nWe will begin with Phase 1. Please propose a layout strategy for the landing page, including key UI elements that define the app\'s purpose, and provide the initial code structure."
  }
}
