  planner_response {
    response: "I have completed **Phase 1: Landing Page Architecture** for the Lumina Media Tracker.\n\n### Technical Architecture & Design Decisions\n1.  **Full-Stack Foundation**: I\'ve implemented an **Express + Vite** hybrid architecture. This ensures that your media data is persisted in a real **SQLite** database (`media_tracker.db`) rather than just in-memory, allowing for a \"real\" application experience from the start.\n2.  **Minimalist Aesthetic**: Following **Design Recipe 8 (Clean Utility)**, the UI uses a neutral palette (`zinc`), high-quality typography (`Inter`), and generous whitespace. This reduces cognitive load, which is essential for a cataloging tool.\n3.  **Responsive Layout**: The `Layout` component uses a fixed, blurred navigation bar and a centered container (`max-w-7xl`) to ensure the app feels premium on both mobile and desktop.\n4.  **Interactive Hero**: The landing page features a dynamic hero section with entrance animations powered by `motion/react`, creating a \"crafted\" feel.\n\n### Key Components Created\n-   `server.ts`: The backend entry point handling API routes and database initialization.\n-   `src/types.ts`: Centralized TypeScript definitions for `MediaItem`, `MediaType`, and `MediaStatus`.\n-   `src/components/Layout.tsx`: The structural wrapper with navigation and footer.\n-   `src/components/Hero.tsx`: An engaging entry point with clear CTAs.\n-   `src/App.tsx`: The main controller managing view states and initial data fetching.\n\n### Data Management Best Practices\n-   **ID Generation**: We use unique IDs for each media item to ensure stable list rendering and precise updates.\n-   **ISO Dates**: All dates are stored as ISO strings in the database to allow for easy sorting and filtering in Phase 3.\n-   **Type Safety**: Enums are used for `MediaType` and `MediaStatus` to prevent data corruption and improve developer experience.\n\n**Phase 1 is now live.** You can navigate between the landing page and the placeholders for the next phases. \n\n**Ready to proceed to Phase 2: Dynamic Input System?** I will implement the modal-based entry form with real-time validation and database integration."
    modified_response: "I have completed **Phase 1: Landing Page Architecture** for the Lumina Media Tracker.\n\n### Technical Architecture & Design Decisions\n1.  **Full-Stack Foundation**: I\'ve implemented an **Express + Vite** hybrid architecture. This ensures that your media data is persisted in a real **SQLite** database (`media_tracker.db`) rather than just in-memory, allowing for a \"real\" application experience from the start.\n2.  **Minimalist Aesthetic**: Following **Design Recipe 8 (Clean Utility)**, the UI uses a neutral palette (`zinc`), high-quality typography (`Inter`), and generous whitespace. This reduces cognitive load, which is essential for a cataloging tool.\n3.  **Responsive Layout**: The `Layout` component uses a fixed, blurred navigation bar and a centered container (`max-w-7xl`) to ensure the app feels premium on both mobile and desktop.\n4.  **Interactive Hero**: The landing page features a dynamic hero section with entrance animations powered by `motion/react`, creating a \"crafted\" feel.\n\n### Key Components Created\n-   `server.ts`: The backend entry point handling API routes and database initialization.\n-   `src/types.ts`: Centralized TypeScript definitions for `MediaItem`, `MediaType`, and `MediaStatus`.\n-   `src/components/Layout.tsx`: The structural wrapper with navigation and footer.\n-   `src/components/Hero.tsx`: An engaging entry point with clear CTAs.\n-   `src/App.tsx`: The main controller managing view states and initial data fetching.\n\n### Data Management Best Practices\n-   **ID Generation**: We use unique IDs for each media item to ensure stable list rendering and precise updates.\n-   **ISO Dates**: All dates are stored as ISO strings in the database to allow for easy sorting and filtering in Phase 3.\n-   **Type Safety**: Enums are used for `MediaType` and `MediaStatus` to prevent data corruption and improve developer experience.\n\n**Phase 1 is now live.** You can navigate between the landing page and the placeholders for the next phases. \n\n**Ready to proceed to Phase 2: Dynamic Input System?** I will implement the modal-based entry form with real-time validation and database integration."
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
    thinking_signature: "\022\263\005\n\260\005\001\276>\366\373\221\370\301#<\301\316\316\272g\202\245\220\016\353\nQ\240R:\254|\316\\xwq\253\315\257L\253\\o\b,\207\210\204\250J\325J\271I\017\312\253\371f\251\001\377\3320\2624kT\357}\005\326 .\243\3218A\335\316x\276\340\035\315FB\026\354\252\036s\221\272\213Y)\256\b\211l\323\374\371\034\351\216x\024,\360\201Y;\252.\244\245\362\342\343{\343)dn\021\214\006\265\276\200\213\364\3321\034w\244*\272\306o-\t,\332\246\222\321>c1\347c\236\325\262\302GIj\000\027\373D\032?k3\3351p\356s_\246\303\\/\376\037H\363\nT\341\304\016\027\032\006o\216\a\305;\262\337\345aN\233\002\252\223<\022nV\246\366ci\\K-\371\277\315\205\355\'<\331\205\205\231l\346\310\356\304Y7O\"L`<\316\3323L\346t\265\324~If\2671`\364\000\0243\320n\330\325TC\026C\370\021G\005\327YP\021\020_\206\343\344\000\343\202\323F\256\216\371\020t\261\346\252\rZy\356\301\031|y\275;k\336K\332\340t\363\020\352\302\004\321mR\333\360\016zh{\310\034\240\222Ms\027\212\335\253\000\342\262\"\300?\235\'\376i@\n\245\214\v\303_\227$\252\212\342\236 \003\v\374\246=\326\2536P\356\177P\225\347\032\t\257T\363Bhpo\375\265\344\263\242\272=A\256\024\b\177\255\251$\206=\251v\205]\357\350K\355\324\351\214,\021\343|\274\371\320\302k,\363\021\354\372\207aj0Jd\246^\2506\334\273\024\227\346\033\005\317\374K\332b<\274\206\325`\f}\"\375)\\QKq&\177\334\202\3656k:\037_WYr\243\355\267g\202\036\223\274b\037L.\232\006uF\361\301\234-\036\261M\322\352\346E0\333\210\274\375\a\2228ao\254\304\270J\037\000\364\222+p\226\223\226\036\344\311\026\321 \362y\332\270\226\245\252$\313\260h\032\031\\\313\321x\r\265\3405\247\205\357\030\2342\355\333\314p\'z3\"\305\251\270\336\343\006\006\fS\263Z\n\363\240c\".\327FK\347zZ\254\255\v\271\276\371\266\221x\206\372|\212)D\221\030\234f\355\354\336SH\226\274\367\002\212\262\261\363\232\256\311\325(\023i\365[%\224S\355q\207|\305\357\243\235g\302\024\2542\003j\330\302\3077\347\353\217*\t\245\031\221]\310\247\273\021+3\220\254\200H\313\237\321\306\254\310\230s\376\261&\237\232\337\2