  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Implementing Dark Theme**\n\nI\'ve begun updating the project files to integrate a dark theme. Specifically, I\'ve modified `src/components/Layout.tsx`. The background color, previously light grey, is now a dark zinc-950, and the text color adjusts to a light zinc-100. Also, I changed the navigation bar\'s background from a slightly transparent white to a transparent dark zinc-900.\n\n\n**Refining Dark Theme Updates**\n\nI\'ve just finished the modifications for `src/components/Layout.tsx`, and now, I\'m integrating adjustments for the dark theme into `src/components/Hero.tsx`. I\'m replacing the backgrounds with a darker tone and updating the text colors to align with the new theme. The goal is to get this implemented systemically, across the codebase. I\'ve also identified a good set of changes for `src/App.tsx`, focusing on text color adaptations. I\'ve tweaked the patterns, as well, for a consistent look. I\'ll get those updates in place, and then move on from there.\n\n\n"
    tool_calls {
