  checkpoint {
    checkpoint_index: 1
    user_intent: "Media Tracker Development\nThe user wants to develop a comprehensive media tracking web application. The current goal is to implement Phase 2: the dynamic input system, which involves designing and integrating a form for adding new media items. This includes handling different media types (movies, series, documentaries, books, games) and their specific input fields, as well as saving the data to the backend."
    session_summary: "The user and I have collaboratively developed the initial version of the \"Lumina Media Tracker\" application. Here\'s a summary of our progress and key information:\n\n**Project Goal:**\nTo create a comprehensive web application for cataloging movies, series, documentaries, books, and console games, featuring a clean, modern, and responsive UI with data persistence and analytics.\n\n**Current Phase:**\nPhase 2: Dynamic Input System. The landing page (Phase 1) is complete and functional.\n\n**Key Features Implemented:**\n\n1.  **Landing Page (Phase 1):**\n    *   **Design:** Minimalist, clean, and modern aesthetic with a dark color scheme.\n    *   **Layout:** Fixed navigation bar, main content area, and footer.\n    *   **Interactivity:** Hero section with animations and clear calls to action.\n    *   **Content:** Displays \"Recent Activity\" (mock data initially, now fetches from the API) and previews for Analytics and Archive sections.\n    *   **Navigation:** Implemented view switching between \'landing\', \'tracker\', \'archive\', and \'analytics\' using `useState` and `AnimatePresence` for smooth transitions.\n\n2.  **Dynamic Input System (Phase 2 - Partially Implemented):**\n    *   **Media Form Component (`MediaForm.tsx`):**\n        *   A modal form for adding new media items.\n        *   Supports different media types: Movie, Series, Documentary, Book, Game.\n        *   **Common Fields:** Title, Type, Status (Planned, In Progress, Completed, Dropped), Rating (1-5 stars), Notes.\n        *   **Type-Specific Fields:**\n            *   **Movies, Series, Documentaries:** Watch Date, Platform (e.g., Netflix, HBO).\n            *   **Books, Games:** Start Date, End Date.\n            *   **Games:** Console (e.g., PS5, Xbox, Switch).\n        *   **UI:** Uses `lucide-react` icons for media types and form elements. Input fields are styled for the dark theme.\n        *   **State Management:** Uses `useState` for form inputs.\n        *   **Animation:** `motion/react` is used for modal entry and exit animations.\n    *   **Integration into `App.tsx`:**\n        *   A button (\"Add Media\") is now present on the landing page and in the \'tracker\' view to open the `MediaForm`.\n        *   State management (`isFormOpen`) controls the visibility of the form.\n        *   The `handleSaveMedia` function is implemented to send new media data to the backend API.\n\n3.  **Backend and Data Persistence:**\n    *   **Technology Stack:** Express.js, Vite, `better-sqlite3`, `tsx`.\n    *   **Database:** SQLite (`media_tracker.db`).\n    *   **Schema (`server.ts`):** The `media_items` table has been updated to include fields for `watchDate`, `startDate`, `endDate`, `platform`, and `console`.\n    *   **API Endpoints:**\n        *   `GET /api/media`: Fetches all media items.\n        *   `POST /api/media`: Adds a new media item to the database, accepting the new type-specific fields.\n        *   `DELETE /api/media/:id`: (Existing, not yet utilized in UI)\n\n**Design Decisions:**\n\n*   **Dark Theme:** A conscious choice for a modern, less intrusive user experience, especially for a cataloging application.\n*   **Component-Based Architecture:** React components are modular and reusable (`Layout`, `Hero`, `MediaForm`).\n*   **TypeScript:** Used for type safety and improved developer experience.\n*   **Tailwind CSS:** Utilized for rapid UI development and consistent styling.\n*   **`motion/react`:** Integrated for subtle animations to enhance user experience.\n*   **Data Structure:** `MediaItem` interface is designed to accommodate diverse media types while maintaining a core set of properties.\n\n**Dependencies:**\n*   **Frontend:** `react`, `react-dom`, `vite`, `@vitejs/plugin-react`, `@tailwindcss/vite`, `tailwindcss`, `autoprefixer`, `lucide-react`, `motion`.\n*   **Backend:** `express`, `better-sqlite3`, `dotenv`, `typescript`, `tsx`.\n*   **API:** `@google/genai` (installed but not yet used).\n\n**Environmental Variables:**\n*   `.env.example` is present, indicating the need for `GEMINI_API_KEY` and `APP_URL`, though these are not yet utilized in the current implementation.\n\n**User Preferences:**\n*   Minimalist, clean aesthetic.\n*   Dark color scheme.\n*   Responsive and user-friendly design.\n*   Logical data structure for sorting and filtering.\n\n**Blockers/Bugs:**\n*   None identified at this stage.\n\n**Next Steps:**\n\n1.  **Complete Phase 2:**\n    *   Implement editing functionality for existing media items.\n    *   Add validation for date fields (e.g., `endDate` should be after `startDate`).\n    *   Refine the UI/UX of the `MediaForm` based on user testing.\n    *   Potentially add image upload/handling for `imageUrl`.\n2.  **Phase 3: Archive & Analytics Dashboard:**\n    *   Develop the archive view to display all media items with robust filtering (by month, category, status, etc.).\n    *   Build the analytics dashboard to visualize consumption data (e.g., charts showing media types consumed over time, average ratings per category).\n3.  **Further Backend Enhancements:**\n    *   Implement search functionality.\n    *   Add more robust error handling and logging.\n    *   Consider pagination for large datasets.\n\nThe application is in a good state, with core functionality for data entry and display established. The dark theme and dynamic input form are successfully integrated."
    code_change_summary: "<edited_file>\n\t<target_file>/metadata.json</target_file>\n\t<lines_modified>4-6</lines_modified>\n\t<edit_summary>Updated the application name and description.</edit_summary>\n</edited_file>\n<edited_file>\n\t<target_file>/package.json</target_file>\n\t<lines_modified>7-8;11-11</lines_modified>\n\t<edit_summary>Updated the dev script to use tsx server.ts and build script to include tsc.</edit_summary>\n</edited_file>\n<edited_file>\n\t<target_file>/src/types.ts</target_file>\n\t<lines_modified>16-26</lines_modified>\n\t<edit_summary>Added specific fields for different media types to the MediaItem interface.</edit_summary>\n</edited_file>\n<edited_file>\n\t<target_file>/server.ts</target_file>\n\t<lines_modified>19-23;40-45</lines_modified>\n\t<edit_summary>Updated the database schema to include new fields for media items and modified the POST route to handle these new fields.</edit_summary>\n</edited_file>\n<edited_file>\n\t<target_file>/src/App.tsx</target_file>\n\t<lines_modified>6-11;18-20;29-31;44-46;50-51;55-57;61-64;70-73;77-105;112-141;145-175</lines_modified>\n\t<edit_summary>Integrated the MediaForm component, added state for form visibility, implemented the handleSaveMedia function, and updated the UI to conditionally render the form and display media details.</edit_summary>\n</edited_file>\n<edited_file>\n\t<target_file>/src/components/Layout.tsx</target_file>\n\t<lines_modified>13-13;15-15;21-21;22-22;24-24;30-30;36-36;42-42;50-50;64-64;66-66;71-71;72-72;73-73</lines_modified>\n\t<edit_summary>Switched the application\'s color scheme to a dark theme, updating background colors, text colors, and element styles.</edit_summary>\n</edited_file>\n<edited_file>\n\t<target_file>/src/components/Hero.tsx</target_file>\n\t<lines_modified>12-12;19-19;22-22;23-23;26-26;33-33;41-41;49-49;51-51;52-52;53-53;54-54;60-60</lines_modified>\n\t<edit_summary>Updated the Hero component to match the dark theme, adjusting background colors, text colors, and icon colors.</edit_summary>\n</edited_file>\n<edited_file>\n\t<target_file>/src/components/MediaForm.tsx</target_file>\n\t<lines_modified>0-175</lines_modified>\n\t<edit_summary>Created the MediaForm component with input fields for various media types, including conditional rendering for type-specific fields and dark theme styling.</edit_summary>\n</edited_file>\n<viewed_file>\n\t<absolute_path>/package.json</absolute_path>\n\t<lines_viewed>1-36</lines_viewed>\n\t<learnings>This file defines the project\'s dependencies and scripts. It was important to check the `scripts` section to ensure the correct commands were being used for development and building, and to verify the installed dependencies.</learnings>\n</viewed_file>\n<viewed_file>\n\t<absolute_path>/server.ts</absolute_path>\n\t<lines_viewed>1-74</lines_viewed>\n\t<learnings>This file contains the Express server setup, API routes, and database interactions. It was crucial for understanding how data is stored and retrieved, and for making necessary modifications to accommodate new fields.</learnings>\n</viewed_file>\n<viewed_file>\n\t<absolute_path>/src/types.ts</absolute_path>\n\t<lines_viewed>1-29</lines_viewed>\n\t<learnings>This file defines the TypeScript interfaces and enums for the application. It was essential for understanding the data structure of `MediaItem` and for updating it to include new fields required for Phase 2.</learnings>\n</viewed_file>\n<viewed_file>\n\t<absolute_path>/src/App.tsx</absolute_path>\n\t<lines_viewed>1-177</lines_viewed>\n\t<learnings>This is the main application component that orchestrates the UI and state management. It was modified to integrate the new `MediaForm`, handle form submission, and display media items with their new details.</learnings>\n</viewed_file>\n<viewed_file>\n\t<absolute_path>/src/components/Layout.tsx</absolute_path>\n\t<lines_viewed>1-80</lines_viewed>\n\t<learnings>This component provides the overall structure of the application, including navigation and the footer. It was modified to implement the dark theme, ensuring consistency across the application.</learnings>\n</viewed_file>\n<viewed_file>\n\t<absolute_path>/src/components/Hero.tsx</absolute_path>\n\t<lines_viewed>1-65</lines_viewed>\n\t<learnings>The Hero component is the landing page\'s main visual element. It was updated to fit the dark theme and to trigger the opening of the media form.</learnings>\n</viewed_file>\n<viewed_file>\n\t<absolute_path>/src/components/MediaForm.tsx</absolute_path>\n\t<lines_viewed>1-168</lines_viewed>\n\t<learnings>This newly created component is responsible for the media input form. It handles user input, type-specific fields, and styling for the dark theme.</learnings>\n</viewed_file>\n<viewed_code_item>\n\t<node_identifier>MediaItem Interface</node_identifier>\n\t<learnings>The `MediaItem` interface in `src/types.ts` was extended to include fields like `watchDate`, `startDate`, `endDate`, `platform`, and `console`, which are necessary for capturing detailed information about different media types.</learnings>\n</viewed_code_item>\n<viewed_code_item>\n\t<node_identifier>server.ts - CREATE TABLE statement</node_identifier>\n\t<learnings>The `CREATE TABLE` statement in `server.ts` was updated to include columns for the new fields (`watchDate`, `startDate`, `endDate`, `platform`, `console`) to persist this data in the SQLite database.</learnings>\n</viewed_code_item>\n<viewed_code_item>\n\t<node_identifier>server.ts - INSERT INTO statement</node_identifier>\n\t<learnings>The `INSERT INTO` statement in the `/api/media` POST route in `server.ts` was modified to accept and insert values for the new fields, ensuring that data from the form is correctly saved.</learnings>\n</viewed_code_item>\n<viewed_code_item>\n\t<node_identifier>App.tsx - handleSaveMedia function</node_identifier>\n\t<learnings>The `handleSaveMedia` function in `App.tsx` was implemented to send the form data to the backend API. It correctly structures the payload, including the new fields, and handles the response, including closing the form and refetching data.</learnings>\n</viewed_code_item>\n<viewed_code_item>\n\t<node_identifier>App.tsx - isFormOpen state and MediaForm rendering</node_identifier>\n\t<learnings>The `isFormOpen` state in `App.tsx` controls the visibility of the `MediaForm`. The `AnimatePresence` component is used for smooth mounting and unmounting of the form, providing a better UX.</learnings>\n</viewed_code_item>\n<viewed_code_item>\n\t<node_identifier>MediaForm Component</node_identifier>\n\t<learnings>The `MediaForm` component in `src/components/MediaForm.tsx` is a self-contained unit for adding media. It manages its own form state, uses conditional rendering for type-specific fields, and applies dark theme styling.</learnings>\n</viewed_code_item>\n<viewed_code_item>\n\t<node_identifier>MediaForm Component - Type Selection Buttons</node_identifier>\n\t<learnings>The buttons for selecting media type in `MediaForm` are styled to be visually distinct when active, providing clear feedback to the user about the currently selected type.</learnings>\n</viewed_code_item>\n<viewed_code_item>\n\t<node_identifier>MediaForm Component - Conditional Field Rendering</node_identifier>\n\t<learnings>The `isVisualMedia` and `isInteractiveMedia` logic within `MediaForm` correctly determines which date fields (`watchDate` vs. `startDate`/`endDate`) and additional fields (`platform` vs. `console`) to display based on the selected media type.</learnings>\n</viewed_code_item>\n<viewed_code_item>\n\t<node_identifier>App.tsx - Display of new media details</node_identifier>\n\t<learnings>The `App.tsx` component was updated to display the new media details (`platform`, `console`, dates) for each item in the \"Recent Activity\" section, using conditional rendering based on the item\'s type.</learnings>\n</viewed_code_item>"
