    response: "I have successfully implemented **Phase 2: Dynamic Input System** with the dark theme and all requested fields.\n\n### Key Features of the New Input System:\n1.  **Context-Aware Fields**: The input window dynamically adjusts its fields based on the selected media type:\n    *   **Movies, TV Shows, Documentaries**: Asks for **Watch Date** and **Streaming Platform** (Netflix, HBO, etc.).\n    *   **Books**: Asks for **Start Date** and **End Date**.\n    *   **Console Games**: Asks for **Start Date**, **End Date**, and the **Specific Console** (PS5, Switch, etc.).\n2.  **Unified Fields**: All media types require a **Title**, **Status** (Planned, In Progress, Completed, Dropped), and a **Personal Rating** (1-5 stars).\n3.  **Real-Time Persistence**: New items are immediately saved to the SQLite database via the Express API and appear in the \"Recent Activity\" section on the landing page.\n4.  **Modern UI/UX**:\n    *   **Animated Transitions**: Smooth field switching using `AnimatePresence`.\n    *   **Glassmorphism**: A blurred backdrop for the modal to maintain focus.\n    *   **Responsive Design**: The form is optimized for both desktop and mobile viewing.\n\n### Technical Implementation:\n*   **Database**: Updated `media_tracker.db` schema to include columns for `watchDate`, `startDate`, `endDate`, `platform`, and `console`.\n*   **Frontend**: Created a specialized `MediaForm` component that manages its own state and communicates with the parent `App` component to trigger data refreshes.\n*   **Icons**: Integrated specific icons for each field (Monitor for platforms, CPU for consoles, Calendar for dates) to improve scannability.\n\n**The input system is now fully operational.** You can click the **\"Add Media\"** button in the navigation bar or the **\"Get Started\"** button in the hero section to try it out.\n\n**Shall we move on to Phase 3: Archive & Analytics Dashboard?** This will involve creating a dedicated view to visualize your history and see statistics about your media consumption."
